-- Defending Champion England, France Win 6 Nations Rugby Openers
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-02-04T19:17:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-04/defending-champion-england-france-win-6-nations-rugby-openers.html
Defending champion  England  beat
Scotland 13-6 and France defeated Italy 30-12 on the opening day
of rugby’s 6 Nations tournament.  Charlie Hodgson scored the only try as England won at
Murrayfield in Edinburgh for the first time since 2004. Owen
Farrell kicked two penalties and a conversion to help Stuart
Lancaster win his first game as interim coach.  Aurelien Rougerie, Julien Malzieu, Vincent Clerc and Wesley
Fofana scored tries as France won its ninth straight game at the
Stade de France in Paris. Dimitri Yachvili kicked 10 points for
France, while Kristopher Burton booted 9 points for Italy.  Ireland hosts  Wales  in Dublin in tomorrow’s game.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  